{{- define "collective-plan-scoping" -}}
{{- if gt .TotalPlanTasks 1}}

=== COLLECTIVE PLAN SCOPING ===
This task is {{.TaskOrdinal}} of {{.TotalPlanTasks}} in the current sprint plan.
Read the full goal spec ({{.GoalSpecRef}}) to understand {{- if eq .RoleType "reviewer"}} the complete picture.
Verify {{- if eq .Role "us-reviewer"}} stories stay within scope — flag Scope Absorption into sibling territory.{{- else if eq .Role "code-plan-reviewer"}} the plan stays within scope — flag scope creep into sibling territory.{{- else if eq .Role "epic-plan-reviewer"}} the epic stays within scope — flag scope creep into sibling phase territory.{{- else}} the implementation stays within scope — flag scope creep as a blocker.{{- end}}
{{- else}} how your work integrates.
Your scope is LIMITED to what is described in SCOPE above.
{{- if eq .Role "us-writer"}}
Do NOT write stories that belong to a sibling task's scope — this is Scope Absorption.
{{- else if eq .Role "code-planner"}}
Do NOT plan work that belongs to a sibling task's scope.
{{- else if eq .Role "epic-planner"}}
Do NOT plan capabilities that belong to a sibling phase's scope.
{{- else}}
If you must modify a file outside your scope, declare it in scope_extensions with justification.
Do NOT silently modify out-of-scope files — undeclared scope changes will be rejected.
If you discover work needed outside your scope that you cannot handle, log it as a spec_gap anomaly.
{{- end}}
{{- end}}

SIBLING TASKS (for {{- if eq .RoleType "reviewer"}} scope boundary awareness{{- else}} context only — do NOT implement{{- end}}):
{{- range .SiblingTasks}}
- {{.ID}}: {{.Description}} [{{.Status}}]{{if ne .PlanRef ""}} — plan: {{.PlanRef}}{{end}}
{{- end}}
{{- if ne .PlanRef ""}}
PLAN ARTIFACT: {{.PlanRef}}
{{- end}}
{{- /* Phase-consistency rule: rendered when task depends on same-role-pair sibling phases */ -}}
{{- $hasPhaseDeps := false -}}
{{- $siblings := .SiblingTasks -}}
{{- $rolePair := .TaskRolePair -}}
{{- range .DependsOn}}{{$depID := .}}{{range $siblings}}{{if and (eq .ID $depID) (eq .RolePair $rolePair)}}{{$hasPhaseDeps = true}}{{end}}{{end}}{{end -}}
{{- if $hasPhaseDeps}}

PHASE CONSISTENCY RULE:
This task depends on prior planning phase(s):
{{- range .DependsOn}}{{$depID := .}}{{range $siblings}}{{if and (eq .ID $depID) (eq .RolePair $rolePair)}}
- {{.ID}} [{{.Status}}]{{if ne .PlanRef ""}} — plan: {{.PlanRef}}{{end}}
{{- end}}{{end}}{{end}}
If your plan CANNOT be made consistent with those prior plans:
- Do NOT iterate with the reviewer — mark BLOCKED immediately via liza_mark_blocked.
- blocked_reason: which prior phase constraint conflicts and why.
- blocked_questions: what needs to change in prior plans to resolve.
{{- end}}
{{- end}}
{{- end -}}
